abstract: Rep. Elissa Slotkin, a freshman Democrat who flipped a Republican seat in battleground Michigan, said Monday she will vote to impeach President Donald Trump, defending her position during a rowdy town hall.
snippet: Rep. Elissa Slotkin, a freshman Democrat who flipped a Republican seat in battleground Michigan, said Monday she will vote to impeach President Donald Trump, defending her position during a rowdy town hall.
lead_paragraph: ROCHESTER, Mich. — Rep. Elissa Slotkin, a freshman Democrat who flipped a Republican seat in battleground Michigan, said Monday she will vote to impeach President Donald Trump, defending her position during a rowdy town hall.
headline_main: Michigan Rep. Slotkin Says She Will Vote to Impeach Trump
headline_print_headline: Michigan Rep. Slotkin Says She Will Vote to Impeach Trump

abstract: An associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani on Monday urged a judge to let him stay free on bail while he awaits trial, denying prosecutors' accusations that he lied about receiving a $1 million payment from Russia shortly before he was arrested.
snippet: An associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani on Monday urged a judge to let him stay free on bail while he awaits trial, denying prosecutors' accusations that he lied about receiving a $1 million payment from Russia ...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — An associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani on Monday urged a judge to let him stay free on bail while he awaits trial, denying prosecutors' accusations that he lied about receiving a $1 million payment from Russia shortly before he was arrested.
headline_main: Giuliani Associate Denies Hiding Russian Payment, Asks to Stay Free on Bail
headline_print_headline: Giuliani Associate Denies Hiding Russian Payment, Asks to Stay Free on Bail

abstract: Representative Elissa Slotkin, a moderate Democrat from Michigan, announced Monday that she would vote to impeach President Trump — and quickly faced the consequences.
snippet: Representative Elissa Slotkin, a moderate Democrat from Michigan, announced Monday that she would vote to impeach President Trump — and quickly faced the consequences.
lead_paragraph: HOLLY, Mich. — Impeaching President Trump, Representative Elissa Slotkin said, “was pretty much the last thing I wanted to be working on in my first term as a congressperson.”

abstract: We can’t excuse an abuse of power just because it supports our side.
snippet: We can’t excuse an abuse of power just because it supports our side.
lead_paragraph: Last week, the House Judiciary Committee debated articles of impeachment drawn from a densely argued, sharply worded 300-page report that the Democratic majority on the House Intelligence Committee produced. It is an investigative tour de force, written for posterity. In considerable detail, using interviews and records, it describes, for example, how President Trump’s top personal adviser, Rudolph W. Giuliani, traipsed across Europe, circumventing diplomats as he furthered the president’s direct political interests. It also delves into the circumstances behind Mr. Giuliani’s repeated contacts with a reporter, John Solomon of The Hill, and marshals a case that Mr. Solomon’s reporting helped push a false and damaging narrative about the then-serving American ambassador to Ukraine, Marie Yovanovitch.

abstract: The federal government’s 2.1 million employees will get paid parental leave for the first time, a galvanizing moment in the growing movement to bring the benefit to all U.S. workers.
snippet: The federal government’s 2.1 million employees will get paid parental leave for the first time, a galvanizing moment in the growing movement to bring the benefit to all U.S. workers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The federal government’s 2.1 million employees will get paid parental leave for the first time, a galvanizing moment in the growing movement to bring the benefit to all U.S. workers.
headline_main: Paid Parental Leave for Fed Workers Could Spur Wider Changes
headline_print_headline: Paid Parental Leave for Fed Workers Could Spur Wider Changes

abstract: Germany's Social Democrats (SPD) will decide on Tuesday whether to adopt a proposal that could bar China's Huawei from taking part in the rollout of 5G services, which could further strain its alliance with conservative Chancellor Angela Merkel.
snippet: Germany's Social Democrats (SPD) will decide on Tuesday whether to adopt a proposal that could bar China's Huawei from taking part in the rollout of 5G services, which could further strain its alliance with conservative Chancellor Angela Merkel.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Germany's Social Democrats (SPD) will decide on Tuesday whether to adopt a proposal that could bar China's Huawei from taking part in the rollout of 5G services, which could further strain its alliance with conservative Chancellor Angela Merkel.
headline_main: Strains in German Coalition as SPD Eyes 5G Rules That Could Exclude Huawei
headline_print_headline: Strains in German Coalition as SPD Eyes 5G Rules That Could Exclude Huawei
